    ///   the singular near-boundary corner.
    /// - `layer_kinds_singular_gap() ŌćÆ layer_kinds_singular()`
    ///   always ŌĆö the subsumption via the `layer_kinds_singular_gap`
    ///   disjunct of the defining union. The singleton-gap
    ///   boundary always sits inside the singular near-boundary
    ///   corner.
    /// - `layer_kinds_singular() ŌćÆ layer_kinds_any_observed()` on
