    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_singular_gap`],
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_full_cover`]) into ONE typed variant tag on
    /// the five-corner [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass`] classifier,
    /// with the cardinality-2 dual-singular collapse baked into the
    /// branching priority (bottom-boundary-first).
    ///
    /// The chain-altitude layer-kind sub-axis coverage-support classifier
    /// peer that **lifts the "support-cardinality-class across altitudes"
    /// projection sideways** from the tier altitude
    /// ([`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_cardinality_class`]) to the
    /// first chain-altitude sub-axis, seeded on the diff altitude by
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_cardinality_class`]. The two
    /// remaining chain-altitude sub-axes
    /// ([`Self::file_formats_support_cardinality_class`] over
    /// [`Self::file_format_histogram`],
    /// [`Self::env_prefix_kinds_support_cardinality_class`] over
    /// [`Self::env_prefix_kind_histogram`]) are the natural next
    /// sideways lifts, mirroring the four-step lift trajectory that the
    /// ten prior boolean projections plus the closed modality-class
    /// classifier row followed to closure across the fully-closed
    /// 5-column grid. Coverage-support classifier row on top of the
    /// closed five-primitive coverage-support boolean algebra
    /// ([`Self::layer_kinds_any_observed`],
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_singular_support`],
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_strict_partial_cover`],
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_singular_gap`],
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_full_cover`]) at the chain layer-kind
    /// sub-axis ŌĆö with this lift the "support-cardinality-class across
    /// altitudes" projection carries one named cube-native seam at
    /// three of the five altitudes / sub-axes (diff, tier, and the
    /// first chain sub-axis).
    ///
    /// **Total classification.** Every chain lands on exactly one of the
    /// five [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass`] variants ŌĆö the
    /// classification is total and disjoint by construction over
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::ALL`]. Direct pin of the
    /// histogram-side total-partition law one altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`3` reachability at the layer-kind sub-axis ŌĆö the
    /// classifier reads witnesses on four of the five variants; the
    /// strict-interior corner is vacuously unreachable.**
    /// [`ConfigSourceKind`] carries three cells, so
    /// `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class()` reads:
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`] on the empty chain
    /// (support `0`); [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`]
    /// on every singleton-support chain (support `1`);
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap`] on every two-kind
    /// partial-cover chain (support `2 = cardinality - 1`); and
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`] on every uniform
    /// three-kind cover (support `3`). The strict-interior variant
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::StrictPartialCover`] is
    /// **vacuously unreachable** on the cardinality-`3` layer-kind
    /// sub-axis ŌĆö the strict interval `[2, cardinality - 2] = [2, 1]`
    /// is empty, so no chain lands on the strict-interior corner.
    /// Matches the shared vacuous-strict-interior convention with
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_strict_partial_cover`] one seam over, and
    /// matches the cardinality-`3` diff-altitude peer
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_cardinality_class`] on the
    /// same cardinality-`3` [`crate::DiffLineKind`] axis in reachability;
    /// the cardinality-`4` tier altitude
    /// ([`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_cardinality_class`])
    /// carries the additional two-tier partial-cover witness on the
    /// strict-interior corner that the cardinality-`3` axis cannot
    /// inhabit.
    ///
    /// **Empty-chain convention** ŌĆö returns
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`] on the empty chain: the
    /// empty chain observes zero cells, so `distinct_cells` reads `0`
    /// and the classifier lands on the empty-boundary corner. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::support_cardinality_class`]'s empty-
    /// histogram convention one altitude down. Peer of
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_cardinality_class`]'s empty-
    /// diff `Empty` polarity on the diff altitude and
    /// [`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_cardinality_class`]'s
    /// empty-map `Empty` polarity on the tier altitude in the same
    /// projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** ŌĆö returns
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`] on every
    /// chain whose observed support is a single [`ConfigSourceKind`]
    /// cell: one observed cell means `distinct_cells` reads `1` and the
    /// classifier lands on the bottom singular-boundary corner. Direct
    /// pin of the histogram-side subsumption `has_singular_support ŌćÆ
    /// support_cardinality_class == SingularSupport` one altitude down,
    /// and peer of the diff-altitude subsumption pinned by
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_cardinality_class`] and the
    /// tier-altitude subsumption pinned by
    /// [`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_cardinality_class`].
    ///
    /// **Uniform three-kind axis-cover convention** ŌĆö returns
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`] on every chain
    /// observing every cell of [`ConfigSourceKind`] at least once:
    /// three observed cells means `distinct_cells` reads `3` and the
    /// classifier lands on the full-cover corner. Peer of the histogram-
    /// side uniform-cover convention one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class() ==
    ///   layer_kind_histogram().support_cardinality_class()` ŌĆö both
    ///   project the same variant off the same primitive; the named
    ///   seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram surface.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().is_empty() ==
    ///   !layer_kinds_any_observed()` ŌĆö the empty-variant peer of the
    ///   chain layer-kind sub-axis "any observed" predicate; the
    ///   classifier's empty-boundary variant coincides with the empty-
    ///   chain row of the coverage-support boolean grid.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().is_singular_support()
    ///   == layer_kinds_singular_support()` ŌĆö the singleton-support
    ///   peer of the chain layer-kind sub-axis boolean on cardinality-
    ///   `>= 3` axes (the full [`ConfigSourceKind`] axis). Both read
    ///   `false` on the empty chain.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().is_singular_gap() ==
    ///   layer_kinds_singular_gap()` ŌĆö the singular-gap peer of the
    ///   chain layer-kind sub-axis boolean on cardinality-`>= 3` axes.
    ///   Both read `false` on the empty chain.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().is_full_cover() ==
    ///   layer_kinds_full_cover()` ŌĆö the full-cover peer of the chain
    ///   layer-kind sub-axis boolean.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().is_strict_partial_cover()
    ///   == layer_kinds_strict_partial_cover()` ŌĆö the strict-interior
    ///   peer of the chain layer-kind sub-axis boolean. Both read
    ///   `false` uniformly on the cardinality-`3` [`ConfigSourceKind`]
    ///   axis (the strict interior is vacuously empty), matching the
    ///   shared vacuous-strict-interior convention.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().is_partial_cover() ==
    ///   layer_kinds_partial_cover()` ŌĆö the compound-partial-cover peer
    ///   via the class-side
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::is_partial_cover`]
    ///   projection; both read the "some but not all observed" middle
    ///   leg of the coverage trichotomy.
    /// - `layer_kinds_singular_support() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class() ==
    ///   SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport` ŌĆö every singleton-
    ///   support chain lands on the bottom singular-boundary corner.
    ///   Direct pin of the histogram-side subsumption one altitude
    ///   down.
    /// - `layer_kinds_singular_gap() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class() ==
    ///   SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap` ŌĆö every singular-gap
    ///   chain (support cardinality `2 = cardinality - 1`) lands on the
    ///   top singular-boundary corner. Reachable on the cardinality-`3`
    ///   [`ConfigSourceKind`] axis.
    /// - `layer_kinds_full_cover() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class() ==
    ///   SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover` ŌĆö every full-cover chain
    ///   lands on the full-cover corner.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.as_ref().len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigSourceKind>()` (the
    /// distinct-cells scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// layer-kind axis carries a fixed three-cell cardinality; the
    /// returned [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass`] fits in a `u8`
    /// discriminant, so the classifier reads off one four-way `if`
    /// chain over the fused distinct-cells scalar ŌĆö no allocation, no
    /// per-cell branching after the support cardinality is built.
    /// Strictly tighter than the five-way `if` ladder over the five
    /// histogram-surface boolean predicates the consumer would
    /// otherwise write.
    #[must_use]
    fn layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class(&self) -> crate::SupportCardinalityClass
    where
        Self: AsRef<[ConfigSource]>,
    {
        self.layer_kind_histogram().support_cardinality_class()
    }

    /// Closed [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance`] bucket variant naming
    /// how far from the support-cardinality boundary this chain's
    /// [`ConfigSourceKind`] histogram lands on the chain layer-kind
    /// sub-axis ŌĆö the three-cell partition of the
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass`] surface. Routes through
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::support_boundary_distance`] one altitude
    /// down ŌĆö the closed-classifier projection that fuses the two
    /// boundary corners ([`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`] +
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`]) into the
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary`] bucket, the two
    /// singular near-boundary corners
    /// ([`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`] +
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap`]) into the
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Singular`] bucket, and the
    /// strict interior [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::StrictPartialCover`]
    /// into the [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::StrictInterior`]
    /// bucket. Equivalently: reads
    /// [`Self::layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class`] one seam over
    /// and projects through the class-side
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::support_boundary_distance`]
    /// three-bucket variant-tag projection ŌĆö both routings are
    /// pointwise equal.
    ///
    /// The chain-altitude layer-kind sub-axis distance-from-boundary
    /// classifier peer that **lifts the "support-boundary-distance
    /// across altitudes" projection sideways** from the tier altitude
    /// ([`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_boundary_distance`]) to
    /// the first chain-altitude sub-axis, seeded on the diff altitude
    /// by [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_boundary_distance`]. The
    /// two remaining chain-altitude sub-axes
    /// ([`Self::file_formats_support_boundary_distance`] over
    /// [`Self::file_format_histogram`],
    /// [`Self::env_prefix_kinds_support_boundary_distance`] over
    /// [`Self::env_prefix_kind_histogram`]) are the natural next
    /// sideways lifts, mirroring the four-step lift trajectory that
    /// the eleven prior boolean projections plus the two closed
    /// classifier rows (modality-class, support-cardinality-class)
    /// followed to closure across the fully-closed 5-column grid. The
    /// distance-from-boundary classifier row on top of the closed
    /// three-primitive distance-from-boundary boolean algebra (the
    /// class-side leg-predicate trio ŌĆö `is_boundary`, `is_singular`,
    /// `is_strict_interior` ŌĆö resolved against the coverage-support
    /// booleans one seam over) at the chain layer-kind sub-axis ŌĆö
    /// with this lift the "support-boundary-distance across altitudes"
    /// projection carries one named cube-native seam at three of the
    /// five altitudes / sub-axes (diff, tier, and the first chain
    /// sub-axis).
    ///
    /// **Total classification.** Every chain lands on exactly one of
    /// the three [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance`] variants ŌĆö the
    /// classification is total and disjoint by construction over
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::ALL`]. Direct pin of the
    /// class-side three-bucket-partition law one altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`3` reachability at the layer-kind sub-axis ŌĆö
    /// the strict-interior bucket is vacuously unreachable.**
    /// [`ConfigSourceKind`] carries three cells, so
    /// `layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance()` reads witnesses on
    /// two of the three variants:
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary`] on the empty chain
    /// (via the [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`] corner) and
    /// on every uniform three-kind cover (via the
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`] corner); and
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Singular`] on every singleton-
    /// support chain (via [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`])
    /// and on every two-kind partial-cover chain (via
    /// [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap`]). The strict-
    /// interior bucket [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::StrictInterior`]
    /// is **vacuously unreachable** on the cardinality-`3` layer-kind
    /// sub-axis ŌĆö the underlying strict-partial-cover corner is itself
    /// vacuous (the strict interval `[2, cardinality - 2] = [2, 1]` is
    /// empty), so no chain lands on the strict-interior bucket.
    /// Matches the shared vacuous-strict-interior reachability profile
    /// with the cardinality-`3` diff-altitude peer
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_boundary_distance`] on the
    /// same cardinality-`3` [`crate::DiffLineKind`] axis; the
    /// cardinality-`4` tier altitude
    /// ([`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_boundary_distance`])
    /// carries the additional two-tier partial-cover witness on the
    /// strict-interior bucket that the cardinality-`3` axis cannot
    /// inhabit.
    ///
    /// **Empty-chain convention** ŌĆö returns
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary`] on the empty
    /// chain: the empty chain observes zero cells, so the underlying
    /// support-cardinality classifier lands on the empty-boundary
    /// corner ([`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`]), which the
    /// class-side projection folds into
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary`]. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::support_boundary_distance`]'s empty-
    /// histogram convention one altitude down. Peer of
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_boundary_distance`]'s empty-
    /// diff `Boundary` polarity on the diff altitude and
    /// [`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_boundary_distance`]'s
    /// empty-map `Boundary` polarity on the tier altitude in the same
    /// projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** ŌĆö returns
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Singular`] on every chain
    /// whose observed support is a single [`ConfigSourceKind`] cell:
    /// the underlying support-cardinality classifier lands on the
    /// bottom singular-boundary corner
    /// ([`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`]), which
    /// the class-side projection folds into
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Singular`]. Direct pin of the
    /// composed subsumption `has_singular_support ŌćÆ
    /// support_boundary_distance == Singular` one altitude down, and
    /// peer of the diff-altitude subsumption pinned by
    /// [`crate::ConfigDiff::kinds_support_boundary_distance`] and the
    /// tier-altitude subsumption pinned by
    /// [`crate::ProvenanceMap::tiers_support_boundary_distance`].
    ///
    /// **Uniform three-kind axis-cover convention** ŌĆö returns
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary`] on every chain
    /// observing every cell of [`ConfigSourceKind`] at least once: the
    /// underlying support-cardinality classifier lands on the full-
    /// cover corner ([`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`]),
    /// which the class-side projection folds into
    /// [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary`]. Peer of the
    /// histogram-side uniform-cover convention one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   layer_kind_histogram().support_boundary_distance()` ŌĆö the
    ///   routing equivalence one altitude down; both project the same
    ///   variant off the same primitive.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   layer_kinds_support_cardinality_class().support_boundary_distance()`
    ///   ŌĆö the *class-side* routing equivalence: reading the support-
    ///   cardinality classifier one seam over and projecting through
    ///   the class-side three-bucket variant-tag projection is
    ///   pointwise equal to reading the histogram-side classifier
    ///   directly. Pins the composition through the chain layer-kind
    ///   sub-axis so consumers holding either classifier reach the
    ///   other without re-routing through the originating histogram.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance().is_boundary() ==
    ///   (!layer_kinds_any_observed() || layer_kinds_full_cover())` ŌĆö
    ///   the boundary-bucket peer of the union of the two boundary
    ///   corners on the chain layer-kind sub-axis.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance().is_singular() ==
    ///   (layer_kinds_singular_support() || layer_kinds_singular_gap())`
    ///   ŌĆö the singular-bucket peer of the union of the two singular
    ///   near-boundary corners on the chain layer-kind sub-axis.
    /// - `layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance().is_strict_interior()
    ///   == layer_kinds_strict_partial_cover()` ŌĆö the strict-interior-
    ///   bucket peer of the strict-partial-cover boolean on the chain
    ///   layer-kind sub-axis. Both read `false` uniformly on the
    ///   cardinality-`3` [`ConfigSourceKind`] axis (the strict interior
    ///   is vacuously empty), matching the shared vacuous-strict-
    ///   interior convention with the cardinality-`3` diff-altitude
    ///   peer; reachability strictly advances one altitude up on the
    ///   cardinality-`4` tier axis where the strict-interior bucket
    ///   inhabits the two-tier partial-cover witness.
    /// - `layer_kinds_full_cover() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary` ŌĆö every full-cover chain
    ///   lands on the boundary bucket via the
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`] corner.
    /// - `!layer_kinds_any_observed() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   SupportBoundaryDistance::Boundary` ŌĆö the empty chain lands on
    ///   the boundary bucket via the
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`] corner.
    /// - `layer_kinds_singular_support() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   SupportBoundaryDistance::Singular` ŌĆö every singleton-support
    ///   chain lands on the singular near-boundary bucket.
    /// - `layer_kinds_singular_gap() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   SupportBoundaryDistance::Singular` ŌĆö every singular-gap chain
    ///   (support cardinality `2 = cardinality - 1`) lands on the
    ///   singular near-boundary bucket via the
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap`] corner.
    /// - `layer_kinds_strict_partial_cover() ŌćÆ
    ///   layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance() ==
    ///   SupportBoundaryDistance::StrictInterior` ŌĆö every strict-
    ///   interior chain lands on the strict-interior bucket via the
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::StrictPartialCover`]
    ///   corner. **Vacuously true** on the cardinality-`3`
    ///   [`ConfigSourceKind`] axis (the premise never fires), matching
    ///   the shared vacuous-strict-interior convention with the
    ///   cardinality-`3` diff-altitude peer; reachability strictly
    ///   advances one altitude up on the cardinality-`4` tier axis
    ///   where the subsumption becomes an inhabited constraint.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.as_ref().len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigSourceKind>()` (the
    /// distinct-cells scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// layer-kind axis carries a fixed three-cell cardinality; the
    /// returned [`crate::SupportBoundaryDistance`] fits in a `u8`
    /// discriminant, so the classifier reads off the same fused
    /// distinct-cells scalar the support-cardinality classifier reads
    /// and projects through one closed three-way `match` on the class-
    /// side variant tag ŌĆö no allocation, no per-cell branching after
    /// the support cardinality is built. Strictly tighter than the
    /// three-way `if` ladder over the class-side leg-predicate trio
    /// the consumer would otherwise write.
    #[must_use]
    fn layer_kinds_support_boundary_distance(&self) -> crate::SupportBoundaryDistance
    where
        Self: AsRef<[ConfigSource]>,
    {
        self.layer_kind_histogram().support_boundary_distance()
    }

    /// Closed [`crate::SupportMagnitudeDirection`] bucket variant naming
    /// which magnitude direction of the support-cardinality interval
    /// this chain's [`ConfigSourceKind`] histogram lands on the chain
    /// layer-kind sub-axis ŌĆö the three-cell partition of the
